%I A390875 #45 Apr 20 2026 17:35:47
%S A390875 59,107821,3899141,137724785
%N A390875 Positive integers k for which the 3-node triangle parity-routing process modulo k, starting from (1,1,1), does not halt for at least one of the 8 routing rules.
%C A390875 Three nodes sit on a triangle, each starting with value 1. At each step, the active node sends its value to its left or right neighbor based on the parity of its value and a per-node rule bit. The receiving node adds the sent value modulo k; if the result is 0, the process halts, otherwise the receiver becomes the new active node. With 3 nodes and 2 choices (left/right) per node, there are 2^3 = 8 possible rule sets. The sequence lists values of n for which at least one of the 8 rule sets causes the process to cycle forever instead of halting.
%C A390875 Verified exhaustively for k <= 137724785. No even k produces a cycle when starting values are (1,1,1) (empirical observation, unproven).
%H A390875 Reed Silverstein, <a href="https://node-sim.vercel.app/?target=59">Parity Lab: Interactive triangle simulation for target 59</a>
%e A390875 For k = 59, it cycles under rules {1,2,3,6} (0-indexed) with entry step 39 and cycle length 194.
%e A390875 For k = 107821, it cycles under rules {4,5} with entry step 156534 and cycle length 37866.
%e A390875 For k = 3899141, it cycles under rules {0,7} with entry step 2059355 and cycle length 1156485.
%e A390875 For k = 137724785, it cycles under rules {4,5} with entry step 296171191 and cycle length 85147918.
%K A390875 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A390875 1,1
